Admonish 
to exhort or caution
Advocate 
N: one who pleads for or defends someone or something or V: to plead for something
Bias 
N: tendency or prejudice or V: to have a strong and often unfair influence on
Expostulate 
to attempt to talk someone out of something
Incline 
1) V: to persuade, 2) V: to bow or bend, or 3) N: a slope
Induce 
to persuade, influence, or cause
Influential 
having the power to change things
Interaction 
1) reciprocal or mutual action or influence or 2) doing things with other people
Susceptible 
easily influenced, affected, or harmed by something (followed by “of” or “to”)